modules.description: This module offers operations for managing associative collections with string keys, supporting modifications like insertion, deletion, and updates, as well as transformations via mapping, filtering, and folding. It works with polymorphic maps (`'a t`) and interoperates with sequences and lists for bulk conversions or iterative processing. Typical use cases include processing JSON-like key-value data, aggregating results from streamed inputs, or validating configurations with dynamic key checks.

This module enables OCaml syntax tree manipulation, input validation, and code generation by handling XML attribute mappings, form element transformations, and AST node creation for templates, exceptions, and modules. It operates on XML trees, OCaml AST structures, and JSON-like data via a polymorphic string-keyed map, supporting tasks like error reporting, location tracking, and bidirectional conversion between OCaml syntax and XML. Specific applications include integrating with the `ppx_ojs` preprocessor for syntax extensions and generating form-based UI components with validated attributes.

This module provides functions for parsing and transforming OCaml syntax trees, mapping XML attributes to OCaml values, and generating code for templates, exceptions, and modules. It works directly with OCaml AST nodes, XML trees, and polymorphic string-keyed maps representing JSON-like data. It is used to implement the `ppx_ojs` preprocessor for syntax extensions and to generate type-safe form components with attribute validation.
